Reasoning: The paper focuses on the design and configuration of applied Web-based systems, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The use of a multicriteria decision-making approach and a lattice-based discrete space suggests a human-computer interaction (cs.HC) aspect to the research. The paper also mentions the design of information systems (cs.DB) and the use of information retrieval techniques (cs.IR) in the context of academic applications. Finally, the paper discusses the design of a corporate system, which could fall under the cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-category.
